wikipedia_page.main: Francis Murphy (6 December 1915 – 12 February 1984) was a Scottish footballer, who played primarily for Celtic at club level.He represented Scotland once, in a 3–1 victory against Netherlands in May 1938, and also played for the Scottish Football League XI once in 1936, scoring on both occasions.
